Millions of Naira have been lost as a trailer conveying crates of beer fell and crashed to the ground in Ekwukobia, Anambra state. The incident which happened on Friday, May 8 was seen as an opportunity by the residents of the community who came out to take advantage of the driver’s plight. In the video posted online, many of the residents can be seen helping themselves to the plethora of fallen beer crates. Watch the video below; Ekwulobia residents troop out to drink to stupor after a trailer of beer fell, yesterday, in Anambra State. : Cent Morata A post shared by  Instablog9ja (@instablog9ja) on May 9, 2020 at 3:49am PDT The Nation By Sandra Umeh   Lagos   -      A petrol tanker spilled its content along the Lagos-Badagry road between Barracks and Onireke in Ojo Local Government area of Lagos in the early hours of Tuesday causing a fire outbreak that consumed seven vehicles. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)… October 2, 2018 In "News" The Divisional Police Officer DPO in charge of Odekpe, Anambra State and two of his men have been kidnapped, The Nation reports. But the Commissioner of Police Mr John Abang, who confirmed the report, said they were not kidnapped but ambushed He also said the three men were rescued immediately.… April 24, 2020 In "News" ...Laments that Disturbing Social Happenings are Compounded, Escalated on Daily Basis by Chronic Leadership Failure of Present Governors in South East By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Southeast Based Coalition of Human Rights & Good Governance Organizations (SBCHROs) has accused Governor of Anambra State, Chief Willie Obiano of being… August 31, 2018 In "News"